1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Bishop J. Gregory Jones on the occasion of his fiftieth year in ministry.
3 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Bishop J. Gregory Jones for his many
4 achievements and to commend him on the occasion of his fiftieth year in ministry; and
5 WHEREAS, Bishop J. Gregory Jones is the son of Reverend Magellan Jones, Jr., and
6 Audrey Moss-Stanley, and he was raised by his maternal grandparents, the late Pastor Joseph
7 and Carrie Moss; and
8 WHEREAS, Bishop Jones began preaching at the age of nine; at the age of eighteen,
9 he became an ordained minister under the auspices of the late Bishop M.C. Jenkins and the
10 All-Nations Pentecostal Churches of God in Christ, Inc.; and
11 WHEREAS, at nineteen years old, Bishop Jones was appointed senior pastor of the
12 Greater Grace Temple in Marlin, Texas, where he served for eighteen years; and
13 WHEREAS, Bishop Jones was ordained as a bishop at the age of twenty-two; and
14 WHEREAS, Bishop Jones founded Eden Worship Center in 2010 and held its first
15 service on July 4; in addition to his ministry, he is an accomplished musician, singer,
16 composer, and author; and
17 WHEREAS, Bishop Jones is married to La'Kica Shae Jones, and they have five
18 children; and
19 WHEREAS, Bishop J. Gregory Jones is a passionate and powerful minister, and he
20 is most deserving of the highest recognition for his inspiring career in ministry.
